A 65 year-old widower from Bondeni, Nakuru county is counting loses after his shop was vandalized by suspected hired goons following an alleged rent dispute between himself and his landlord. According to eye witnesses, a group of goons vandalized the shop at around 5AM, making away with merchandize. The businessman,  Mathenge Nderitu says he has lost goods worth 200,000 shillings, calling on police to investigate the incident. He claims this a move to frustrate him out of the premises, despite a court order baring the  owner from evicting or harassing him. 